        <Description>VDR, Video Disc Recorder, enables you to build a powerful set-top box on you own using Linux and a DVB card. It incorporates basic features, such as watching TV, recording and time-shifting, plus advanced features, including MP3/Ogg playback, playback of all video formats supported by MPlayer and backup of the recorded material to MPEG-4, video CD or DVD.</Description>
